[The Republic of the Marshall Islands has a population of approximately 61
000 living on 29 coral atolls and 5 small low-lying islands in the central
Pacific, mid-way between Hawaii and Australia. This is the first report of
cholera in the Marshall Islands carried by ProMED-mail. Readers are
referred to the PACNET outbreak and control information for cholera
(<http://www.spc.int/phs/>) for detailed information on the regional
guidelines for cholera outbreak control. If our friends at PACNET have
more information on this reported outbreak it would be very much
appreciated. - Mod.MPP
